30/01/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Five Bulgarian nurses, who together with a Palestinian doctor were sentenced to death in Libya following a controversial HIV infection trial, may face new charges of slandering Libyan police, according to the Libyan lawyer representing the medics, Osman Bizanti. The nurses have testified that police tortured them into confessions. On Tuesday (January 30th), the Bulgarian media quoted Bizanti as saying that the nurses would be interrogated on February 11th regarding the new charges. 
Sofia's City Prosecutor Nikolay Kokinov meanwhile confirmed that an official procedure against Libyan officers suspected of torturing the nurses would be launched on Wednesday. Charges would be filed against 11 people. (BNR, Darik - 30/01/07)
